<title type="html"><![CDATA[NES Kung Fu Heroes Title Screen Rom Hack.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6057&amp;p=56694#p56694"><![CDATA[
Since, like tepples said, each game uses its own format for storing things, you won't find a generic application to edit this kind of stuff. These types of application are always game-specific, because each game has to be reverse engineered individually.<br /><br />If you don't have any knowledge of 6502 assembly or the architecture of the NES, it will be hard to do it on your own. What you need is an emulator with a debugger (such as FCEUXD or Nintendulator). With it you need to set up a breakpoint for name table writes (program execution will stop when the name tables are written to), so that you can look at what the program is doing at that moment and try to figure out where it's copying the title screen data from and in what format it's stored. Once you figure that out you just have to encode the new screen using the same format and replace the old one.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Tue Feb 16, 2010 5:35 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
