<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6057&amp;p=56690#p56690"><![CDATA[
What would be the best way to go about hacking the title screen from the NES game Kung Fu Heroes?<br /><br />I'm a little confused about arranging the title screen.  I understand the concepts of sprite and tile editing, and having limited tile space in the chr file. I'm not worried about having to subtract in-game graphical data, at the moment since the title screen is more important to me.<br /><br />But I'm not able to find much information on title screen creation.  I've looked at applications such as SnowBros title screen arranger, and I'm currently looking at p8nes, but they seem more for creating your own program from scratch instead of editing a pre-existing rom file.<br /><br />any help, suggestions, or links to tutorials would be greatly appreciated.<br /><br />Thanks in advance, MattDC.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4237">mattdc</a> — Tue Feb 16, 2010 4:56 pm</p><hr />
